Determining whether a work of authorship is a joint work  has important implications 
for the ownership of the copyright and the term of the copyright.  
The authors of a joint wo rk jointly own the copyright in each other’s contributions and 
each author owns an undivided interest in the copyright for the work as a whole. 17 
