The Copyright Act  states that “a work is ‘created’ when it is fixed in a copy or 
phonorecord for the first time.” 17 U.S.C. § 101  (definition of “created”). The statute 
states that “where a work is prep ared over a period of time, the portion of [the work] 
that has been fixed at any particular time constitutes the work as of that time.” Id. It also 
states that “where the work has been prepared in different versions, each version 
constitutes a separate wor k.” Id. 
